Project Proposal SODV3203
Group 12 – Candace Arriola and Janine Neville
Due Date: March 5, 2023

Github link: https://github.com/JNevile/SODV3203-Project-2023/tree/main/Proposal 
Description of App: 
•	Broad topic for app:   
Foodbank finding app that assists food seekers and food donors:
For food seekers, the app locates nearby food resources including food banks that are free, and food markets that are low cost, 
available to residents in the Calgary, Alberta area. 
o	For food donors, the app provides searchable information regarding foodbank locations nearby that are accepting donations.

•	Name for app:        FoodShare

Features of App: 
•	Data that is persisted locally:  
o	Food bank locations;
o	Foodbank operating hours;
o	Foodbank contact information;
o	Types of foods offered (Halal, gluten free, lactose free); and 
o	Types of food donations accepted.
•	Data that is linked: Money saving food options available through sites linked with buttons: 
o	Fresh Routes www.freshroutes.ca
o	Good Food Box https://www.ckpcalgary.ca/goodfoodbox
•	Third party API: 
o	We will have a third party API for Google Maps allowing users to see the Google Map location of the foodbanks. 



Screens of App: 
1.	Login screen  
a.	Login option using email and password
b.	Signup option for new users
c.	Forgot password link
d.	Privacy policy link

2.	Home page  
a.	Buttons that link to low-cost food programs: 
i.	Good Food Box affordable produce program 
ii.	Fresh Routes food markets 
b.	Search icon link

3.	Search page 
a.	Search for foodbanks by entering your address

4.	Results from search page
a.	Listing of nearby foodbanks displaying:
i.	Foodbank name
ii.	Foodbank civic address
 
5.	Optional expanded detailed search result page 
a.	Foodbank details provided in the expanded result page include:
i.	Foodbank name
ii.	Location
iii.	Contact information:  (telephone number, link to website)
b.	Google map displaying foodbank location
